column1: Comes in normal CMS package and has normal instruction manual.
Besides the normal minifigure parts you get a brown wand and a hot dog.

Her figure is is really good. The hat/hair mold piece is really nice. Also the detail on the rest of her body is really nice. The layers of clothing is really nice. Also I think she has a necklace of some kind around her neck as well.
Overall this is another great CMS Wizarding World character. The detail on her is really nice. Also the new hat/hair piece was nice. Getting the hotdog was a nice addition. Overall I'
column2: m giving it a 5 star rating.&nbsp

The opening scene outside the bank in New York City is where this variant of Tina can be found, here she comes with all the same parts as her LEGO Dimensions counterpart, including the new hat/hair combination, but the colours are quite different.

column1: Dual-Moulded legs are used once again to complete the look of a jacket draped down bast the belt line, this time in a light blue-black combination. Her coat is printed to exacting detail, and she features a suitable under jacket and shirt visible as well. She includes a smiling face and a more sombre frowning expression. Her accessories include her wand, a Hot Dog Bun element and a dark maroon sausage for the bun.
Overall a very nice variant of Tina and worth tracking down for fans of the Fantastic Beasts franchise. Recommended.
